    content: `
      <p class="lead">The Qatar Distribution Company (QDC) is the government-licensed retailer for take-home alcohol purchases in Qatar. Unlike many countries where alcohol is sold in supermarkets and off-licences, Qatar concentrates all non-hotel alcohol retail through QDC's dedicated stores. If you hold a valid QDC permit, knowing where your nearest branch is — and when it's open — is essential.</p>

      <h2 id="about-qdc">About QDC Branches in Qatar</h2>
      <p>QDC does not operate a single large central warehouse — instead, it maintains a network of stores distributed to serve the main residential and industrial areas of Qatar. The stores vary in size, but all stock the same core range of beer, wine, spirits, and associated products. Stock levels can vary between branches, with the larger Abu Hamour main store carrying the widest selection.</p>
      <p>All QDC stores require a valid QDC permit for purchase. You cannot enter without one, and you cannot purchase over your monthly permit allowance regardless of which branch you use. Permit allowances are tracked centrally.</p>

      <h2 id="doha-branches">QDC Branches in Doha</h2>

      <h3>QDC Abu Hamour (Main Store)</h3>
      <p>The flagship QDC store in Abu Hamour is the largest and best-stocked branch. Located off the Industrial Area Road near Salwa Road, Abu Hamour is conveniently positioned for residents of the southern and central Doha suburbs.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Location:</strong> Abu Hamour, off Industrial Area Road (near Salwa Road intersection)</li>
        <li><strong>Opening hours:</strong> Monday–Thursday: 9:00 AM – 9:00 PM</li>
        <li><strong>Saturday:</strong> 9:00 AM – 9:00 PM</li>
        <li><strong>Friday:</strong> 2:00 PM – 9:00 PM</li>
        <li><strong>Sunday:</strong> 9:00 AM – 9:00 PM</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>QDC Salwa Road Branch</h3>
      <p>The Salwa Road branch serves residents in the Salwa Road corridor and surrounding neighbourhoods. It stocks a solid range and is typically less crowded than Abu Hamour during peak periods.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Location:</strong> Salwa Road, southern Doha</li>
        <li><strong>Opening hours:</strong> Monday–Thursday, Saturday–Sunday: 9:00 AM – 9:00 PM</li>
        <li><strong>Friday:</strong> 2:00 PM – 9:00 PM</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="north-qatar">QDC Branches Outside Doha</h2>

      <h3>QDC Al Khor</h3>
      <p>Serving the large expat community in the Al Khor area north of Doha, particularly those working in industrial and construction sectors in that region. Al Khor has a significant South Asian and Southeast Asian expat population.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Location:</strong> Al Khor Industrial Area</li>
        <li><strong>Opening hours:</strong> Monday–Thursday, Saturday–Sunday: 9:00 AM – 9:00 PM</li>
        <li><strong>Friday:</strong> 2:00 PM – 9:00 PM</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>QDC Ras Laffan</h3>
      <p>The Ras Laffan branch is positioned to serve the enormous industrial city of Ras Laffan, home to Qatar's major LNG processing plants and a large number of international workers employed in the energy sector. Access requires entry to the Ras Laffan Industrial City — ensure you have the appropriate visitor or resident credentials for the area.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Location:</strong> Ras Laffan Industrial City</li>
        <li><strong>Opening hours:</strong> Monday–Thursday, Saturday–Sunday: 9:00 AM – 9:00 PM</li>
        <li><strong>Friday:</strong> 2:00 PM – 9:00 PM</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>QDC Um Alhoul (Mesaieed)</h3>
      <p>The Um Alhoul branch serves the Mesaieed Industrial City and surrounding southern Qatar industrial zone. Like Ras Laffan, this area has a large expat workforce in energy and industrial sectors.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Location:</strong> Um Alhoul / Mesaieed Industrial Area</li>
        <li><strong>Opening hours:</strong> Monday–Thursday, Saturday–Sunday: 9:00 AM – 9:00 PM</li>
        <li><strong>Friday:</strong> 2:00 PM – 9:00 PM</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="opening-hours">Standard QDC Opening Hours</h2>
      <p>Across all QDC branches, the standard operating hours in 2026 are:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Monday – Thursday:</strong> 9:00 AM – 9:00 PM</li>
        <li><strong>Saturday – Sunday:</strong> 9:00 AM – 9:00 PM</li>
        <li><strong>Friday:</strong> 2:00 PM – 9:00 PM (shortened due to Friday prayers)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Note: All QDC stores close during Ramadan day hours and may operate reduced hours throughout the Ramadan month. Stores are also closed on official Qatar public holidays. Always verify current hours via the QDC website or by calling the branch directly before making a special trip.</p>

      <h2 id="permit-requirements">QDC Permit Requirements</h2>
      <p>To purchase from any QDC branch, you must:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Be a non-Muslim resident of Qatar (QID holder)</li>
        <li>Hold a valid QDC permit card</li>
        <li>Have remaining monthly allowance on your permit</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Tourists cannot purchase from QDC — this is strictly for residents. Tourists may purchase alcohol only at licensed hotel bars and restaurants. The QDC permit is obtained through the QDC website with your Qatar ID, employer NOC, and salary verification. The process takes a few days. Monthly spending limits apply and vary by salary level.</p>

      <h2 id="what-to-expect">What to Expect at a QDC Store</h2>
      <p>QDC stores are professional retail environments — well-lit, organized, with product displayed in standard retail fashion. Staff are helpful and multi-lingual (English, Arabic, and various South Asian languages are spoken across branches). Products are categorized by type: beer section, wine section, spirits section, and often a small accessories/mixers area.</p>
      <p>Queues can be long on Thursday afternoons (the Gulf equivalent of Friday afternoon before the weekend) and on the day before major public holidays. Plan around peak times if possible. Payment is accepted by card and cash; most branches now have card payment terminals.</p>

      <h2 id="stock">Stock and Availability</h2>
      <p>The Abu Hamour main store has the widest product selection. Specialty and premium items are more reliably stocked there than at the satellite branches. If you're looking for a specific premium whisky, particular wine, or specialty beer, call ahead or visit Abu Hamour. Popular everyday items (Heineken, Jack Daniel's, standard wines) are consistently available at all branches.</p>

      <h2 id="faq">FAQ: QDC Store Locations</h2>

      <h3>Where is QDC in Doha?</h3>
      <p>The main QDC store is in Abu Hamour, off the Industrial Area Road near Salwa Road. There is also a branch on Salwa Road itself. Outside Doha, QDC branches operate in Al Khor, Ras Laffan (industrial city), and Um Alhoul (Mesaieed). The Abu Hamour main store is the best-stocked and most accessible for Doha residents.</p>
    `,
